    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash then add your <strong>spinach </strong>to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water </strong>all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach </strong>under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it’s cool</p><p>Once<strong> </strong>the<strong> spinach</strong> is cool, squeeze as much water out of it as you can, then add it to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>of your<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) – this is your <strong>sesame spinach</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
